Present location: INSTITUT DE PAPYROLOGIE ET D'ÉGYPTOLOGIE, UNIVERSITÉ DE LILLE III [02/049] LILLE
Name: Mummy breast cover
Description: Rectangular mummy breast cover, slightly trapezoid-shaped at the bottom. From top to bottom first a frieze of khekeru motifs (compare with L 1382). Then three registers of mummiform gods facing the middle. First register: Amset and Hepi. Second register: Qebehsenuf and Duamutef. Third register: two ram-headed gods. The contours are black, the background is brick-red.
